title: New Way Now: Costco processes bulk-size data with AI for better member experience
author: Google Cloud
description:
*Featured in this video:* Harish Rao, Global VP of Data and Analytics for Costco Wholesale

*Executive summary:* Beloved bulk retailer Costco operates more than 900 warehouses globally, with members getting discounts on everything from food to flights. To serve its members with great experiences, value, and products across any channel — in-person, via email, mobile app, or marketplace — the data team needed to build a member 360 view. Costco chose Google Cloud’s data and AI tools and partnered with Accenture to build its Unified Data Platform. The new platform brings trusted data to its 175,000 users, helping them to make better, faster decisions. And suppliers can better understand member behavior through aggregated data, all with the same goal: bringing value to members and delighting them with the merchandise in any Costco warehouse. Using Vertex and Gemini AI capabilities was foundational to the new platform’s ability to empower and expand teams’ work.

*Challenge:* Costco maintains massive amounts of data and needed a modern data and AI platform to add even more innovation, efficiency, and flexibility to help its teams meet their shared goal of bringing value to members. With so many partners, hyperscalers, and technologies available, and with so much data, Costco enlisted Accenture’s help in researching and creating the right omnichannel solution.

*Solution:* Costco knew they would need a large data and AI footprint, so Google Cloud’s product depth, hyperscale, cost-effectiveness, and native capabilities were the right fit. Costco’s team built a robust platform, allowing them to democratize data to teams across the company and open up new opportunities, such as helping merchandisers understand sales and inventory positions, track promotion performance, and improve return and other processes.

*Results:* The data team has already seen short-term wins with its unified platform, such as cutting the time required to create new audiences from several weeks to 30 minutes. Suppliers can access aggregated data about member shopping behavior to tailor their offerings. In the longer term, Costco is using data and AI technology to bring more value to members and to the bottom line. As Costco’s leadership prepares to profitably double the company size in the next decade, AI capabilities will be crucial for omnichannel measurement, flexibility, and speed.

*Key takeaways and highlights from our interview with Harish Rao, Global VP of Data and Analytics for Costco Wholesale:*

→ “Costco's philosophy is to think about continuous improvement. This partnership is not just, ‘scale and you’re done.’ It’s about continuous innovation to deliver superior member experience. That is who we are at Costco, and that applies to everything.” 

→ “The digital transformation journey is nothing generic that you can pick from. It all depends on your core values and core principles. We go back to our core value proposition of delivering superior member experience, delivering great product and great value. This is a great opportunity for Costco to look at a complete 360-degree view of our members.”

→ “The expectation is to double the company over the next decade. Imagine when you’re a $500 billion enterprise, what does that really look like? The business model is not just to drive a broader revenue model. It goes back to how we drive more value to our members and suppliers.”

*Google Cloud products used:* Vertex AI, Gemini, BigQuery, Bigtable

author: Google Cloud
description:
Get the highlight from our recent keynote: We're excited to announce two major updates to the Google Cloud compute portfolio.

description:

This video unveils two major updates to the Google Cloud compute portfolio: the Ironwood TPU platform and new Axion Arm-based processors.

Learn how Ironwood, our 7th-generation TPU, delivers breakthrough performance and energy efficiency for large-scale model serving and training. Mark details how Ironwood functions as a complete system—part of our AI Hypercomputer—with innovations in networking (ICI & OCS), liquid cooling, and software (vLLM, GKE Inference Gateway).

Then, discover how the new N4A and C4A.metal Axion VMs provide price-performance for the general-purpose workloads that support your AI applications, from data preprocessing to web serving.
See how Google's full-stack, co-designed approach is delivering efficiency gains and powering the future of AI for customers and for Google's own products like Gemini, Search, and YouTube.

title: Conversational Analytics API
author: Google Cloud
description:
Get started today by following our documentation and unlock the speed of AI for your data: https://cloud.google.com/gemini/docs/conversational-analytics-api/overview

The Looker Conversational Analytics API provides a transformative way to interact with data, moving beyond traditional dashboards by allowing users to ask questions in natural language (like "Show me top-selling products last quarter"). Powered by Gemini for Google Cloud, the API leverages the Looker semantic layer (LookML) to ensure that every query is accurate, governed, and based on consistent business definitions, thus acting as a single source of truth. This technology empowers developers to embed trusted, AI-powered analytics directly into custom applications, internal portals, or workflows—eliminating context switching, democratizing data access, and ultimately accelerating the speed at which organizations can make reliable, data-driven decisions.

title: New Way Now: Mobile services get smarter at LG U+ with help from Google AI
author: Google Cloud
description:
*Featured in this video:* SeokYoung Lee, Director, Head of Mobile Agent Services at LG U+

*Executive summary:* Mobile network operator LG U+ chose Google Cloud AI to enhance on-device features for its more than 18 million subscribers across South Korea. As LG U+ continually works to bring customers convenient, easy-to-use mobile devices, they’ve used Gemini and Vertex AI to add call summarization, visual call interfaces, spam detection, and AI call answering for users. In the competitive telecom market, and as LG U+ prepares for international expansion, the company chose Google AI products to differentiate its services and grow revenue. 

*Challenge:* LG U+ aimed to expand its services beyond South Korea, but needed to add to its existing capabilities quickly to serve users in real time with helpful, convenient AI features.
 
*Solution:* The mobile agent services team integrated Gemini into its ixi-O phone agent for more actionable AI that can understand user intent and respond accordingly. The LG U+ ixi-O One agent pairs its own device AI — which transcribes and records calls in real time — with Gemini, which performs sophisticated analysis to summarize conversations and suggest follow-up actions. Next, the mobile agent team will use Vertex AI to add features that recommend responses during calls based on content searches, as well as retrieve relevant locations, objects and contextual information. 

*Results:* With newly expanded AI capabilities, LG U+ will expand internationally, partnering with both Google and other telecom companies. The team’s plans for the coming year include building even deeper data-driven customer understanding into its products and creating an advanced autonomous agent. 

*Key takeaways and highlights from our interview with SeokYoung Lee, Director, Head of Mobile Agent Services at LG U+:*

→ “Our team’s motto is ‘turning imagination into reality.’ Google plays two key roles in this: first is enhancing our imagination, and second is providing practical technologies and solutions that make our ideas real.” 

→ “At LG U+, gen AI and Vertex AI are helping us with a smarter call agent, ixi-O. The problems we aim to solve with ixi-O One were not new, but solving them with AI was incredibly exciting.”

→ “AI allows everyone to start again from the same starting line. Even large businesses can be completely transformed by AI. Telecom companies have been offering similar services, but AI can create entirely new differentiation.”

→ “The most valuable benefit we get from collaborating with Google is that Google has a complete stack of AI. For example, Google Cloud has AI Hypercomputer and research and models and also has Vertex AI to build an agile agent.”

*Google Cloud products used:* Gemini, Vertex AI
